§ HARM-SHAPE attestation :
    The amplifier as-specified ⊗ produces NO :
      • dark-pattern UI (amplifier is passive shading + per-fragment evaluator)
      • engagement-loop optimization (amplifier ¬ session-time-aware ; pure-fn-of-input)
      • surveillance (amplifier ¬ telemetry-emitting on critical-path ; cache thread-local)
      • coercion (amplifier ¬ player-state-mutating ; no Σ-state read except mask)
      • discrimination (amplifier applies-uniformly-to-all-public-fragments)
      • hidden-content (amplifier-output bound-to-spectral-pipe ⊗ ¬ subliminal)
      • instantiation-hazard (amplifier ¬ agent-perspective-instantiating)
      • per-viewer-fingerprinting (amplifier-cache key ¬ player-Φ ; thread-local only)

§ DETERMINISM CONTRACT (§ V.3 (d) reversibility) :
    R! amplifier ⊗ pure-function-of (world_pos, view_dir, base_sdf_grad, budget, kan_weights)
    R! NO temporal-hash, NO RNG, NO frame-counter
    R! same-input → same-output ⊗ frame-deterministic
    ✓ pinned by `flicker_stability_*` + `pixel_determinism_one_thousand_calls` tests

§ SOVEREIGNTY CONTRACT (§ V.3 (d) sovereignty) :
    R! amplifier ¬ blurs-other-Sovereign's body @ Σ-private-region
    R! Σ-private fragments → AmplifiedFragment::ZERO BEFORE any KAN-network touches input vector
    ✓ pinned by `sigma_private_always_zero` + `sigma_private_emits_zero` tests

§ BUDGET CONTRACT (§ Stage-7 budget @ Quest-3) :
    R! per-fragment cost ≤ 1.2 ms / frame @ Quest-3
    R! per-fragment cost ≤ 1.0 ms / frame @ Vision-Pro
    ✓ pinned by `per_fragment_below_budget` test
    ✓ at tier-1 (CoopMatrix) ⊗ ~150 ns per fragment ⊗ ~8000 fragments fit budget

